The paper deals with multi-task learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on designing a new convex optimization formulation for multi-task learning, which falls under the category of convex optimization. The paper also mentions simulations on synthetic examples and on the IEDB MHC-I binding dataset, which suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence, computer vision, computational linguistics, and statistics.
